<A NAME = "AK3642"></A><H3><CENTER>S.652</CENTER>
</H2><P><A NAME = "AK3647"></A><H3><CENTER>Subtitle B--Violence</CENTER>
</H4><P><A NAME = "AK3650"></A><H3>SEC. 551. PARENTAL CHOICE IN TELEVISION PROGRAMMING.
</H3><P><A HREF = "SPP160.HTM#AO365310"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Congress makes following findings <P>
<A HREF = "SPP160.HTM#AO36555"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Television influences children's perception of values and behavior being common and acceptable in society <P>
<A NAME = "AE12980"></A><A HREF = "SPP160.HTM#AO36575"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Television station operators, cable television system operators and video programmers to follow practices in connection with video programming <P>
<A HREF = "SPP160.HTM#AO365759"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Television broadcast and cable programming established pervasive presence in lives of American children <P>
<A NAME = "AE13000"></A><A HREF = "SPP160.HTM#AO36597"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Average American child exposed to 25 hours of television each week and children exposed <P>
<A HREF = "SPP160.HTM#AO36615"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Studies having shown that children exposed to violent video programming at young age having higher tendency for violent and aggressive behavior later in life than children not exposed and children exposed to violent video programming <P>
<A HREF = "SPP160.HTM#AO36635"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Children in United States exposed to estimated 8,000 murders and 100,000 acts of violence on television by time child completes elementary school <P>
<A HREF = "SPP160.HTM#AO36655"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Studies indicate that children affected by pervasiveness and casual treatment of sexual material on television eroding ability of parents to develop responsible attitudes and behavior in children <P>
<A NAME = "AE13040"></A><A NAME = "AE13040"></A><A HREF = "SPP160.HTM#AO36675"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Parents express grave concern over violent and sexual video programming and support technology to give greater control to block video programming in home <P>
<A NAME = "AE13050"></A><A NAME = "AE13050"></A><A HREF = "SPP160.HTM#AO366911"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Compelling governmental interest in empowering parents to limit negative influences of video programming being harmful to children <P>
<A NAME = "AE13060"></A><A HREF = "SPP161.HTM#AO36715"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Providing parents with timely information about nature of video programming and technological tools that allow to block violent, sexual or other programming <P>
<A NAME = "AE13070"></A><A HREF = "SPP161.HTM#AO36755"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>AMENDMENT-Section 303 amended by adding at end following <P>
<A HREF = "SPP161.HTM#AO367910"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>On basis of recommendations from advisory committee established by Commission in accordance with section of Telecommunications Act of 1996 <P>
<A HREF = "SPP161.HTM#AO367963"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Guidelines and recommended procedures for identification and rating of video programming that contains sexual, violent or other indecent material about <P>
<A NAME = "AE13100"></A><A HREF = "SPP161.HTM#AO36818"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>With respect to video programming rated and consultation with television industry <P>
<A HREF = "SPP161.HTM#AO368314"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>In establishing advisory committee for purposes of amendment made by paragraph of subsection <P>
<A NAME = "AE13120"></A><A NAME = "AE13120"></A><A NAME = "AE13120"></A><A NAME = "AE13120"></A><A HREF = "SPP161.HTM#AO36855"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Ensure that committee composed of parents, television broadcasters, television programming producers, cable operators, appropriate public interest groups and other interested individuals from private sector and fairly balanced in terms of political affiliation and functions to be performed by committee <P>
<A NAME = "AK3689"></A><H3><CENTER>S.652</CENTER>
</H2><P><A NAME = "AK3694"></A><H3>SEC. 551. PARENTAL CHOICE IN TELEVISION PROGRAMMING.
</H3><P><A HREF = "SPP162.HTM#AO369710"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Congress makes following findings <P>
<A HREF = "SPP162.HTM#AO36995"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Television influences children's perception of values and behavior being common and acceptable in society <P>
<A HREF = "SPP162.HTM#AO37015"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Television station operators, cable television system operators and video programmers to follow practices in connection with video programming <P>
<A HREF = "SPP162.HTM#AO370159"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Television broadcast and cable programming established pervasive presence in lives of American children <P>
<A HREF = "SPP162.HTM#AO37037"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Average American child exposed to 25 hours of television each week and children exposed <P>
<A HREF = "SPP162.HTM#AO37055"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Studies having shown that children exposed to violent video programming at young age having higher tendency for violent and aggressive behavior later in life than children not exposed and children exposed to violent video programming <P>
<A HREF = "SPP162.HTM#AO37075"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Children in United States exposed to estimated 8,000 murders and 100,000 acts of violence on television by time child completes elementary school <P>
<A HREF = "SPP162.HTM#AO37095"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Studies indicate that children affected by pervasiveness and casual treatment of sexual material on television eroding ability of parents to develop responsible attitudes and behavior in children <P>
<A HREF = "SPP162.HTM#AO37115"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Parents express grave concern over violent and sexual video programming and support technology to give greater control to block video programming in home <P>
<A HREF = "SPP162.HTM#AO371311"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Compelling governmental interest in empowering parents to limit negative influences of video programming being harmful to children <P>
<A HREF = "SPP162.HTM#AO37155"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Providing parents with timely information about nature of video programming and technological tools that allow to block violent, sexual or other programming <P>
<A HREF = "SPP163.HTM#AO37195"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>AMENDMENT-Section 303 amended by adding at end following <P>
<A HREF = "SPP163.HTM#AO372310"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>On basis of recommendations from advisory committee established by Commission in accordance with section of Telecommunications Act of 1996 <P>
<A HREF = "SPP163.HTM#AO372363"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Guidelines and recommended procedures for identification and rating of video programming that contains sexual, violent or other indecent material about <P>
<A HREF = "SPP163.HTM#AO37258"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>With respect to video programming rated and consultation with television industry <P>
<A HREF = "SPP163.HTM#AO372714"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>In establishing advisory committee for purposes of amendment made by paragraph of subsection <P>
<A HREF = "SPP163.HTM#AO37295"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Ensure that committee composed of parents, television broadcasters, television programming producers, cable operators, appropriate public interest groups and other interested individuals from private sector and fairly balanced in terms of political affiliation and functions to be performed by committee <P>
<A NAME = "AK3733"></A><H3><CENTER>S.652</CENTER>
</H2><P><A NAME = "AK3738"></A><H3>SEC. 552. TECHNOLOGY FUND.
</H3><P><A NAME = "AE13340"></A><A HREF = "SPP164.HTM#AO37435"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Establish technology fund to encourage television and electronics equipment manufacturers to facilitate development of technology to empower parents to block programming <P>
<A HREF = "SPP164.HTM#AO374358"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Deem inappropriate for children and encourage availability to low income parents <P>
<A HREF = "SPP164.HTM#AO37475"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Establish and promote effective procedures, standards, systems, advisories or other mechanisms for ensuring that users having easy and complete access to information necessary effectively to utilize blocking technology and encourage availability to low income parents <P>
<A NAME = "AK3749"></A><H3><CENTER>Subtitle C--Judicial Review</CENTER>
</H4><P><A NAME = "AK3752"></A><H3>SEC. 561. EXPEDITED REVIEW.
</H3><P><A NAME = "AE13390"></A><A HREF = "SPP164.HTM#AO375550"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Title or amendment made by title or provision to be heard by district court of 3 judges convened pursuant to provisions of section 2284 of title 28, United States Code <P>
<A HREF = "SPP164.HTM#AO375737"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Order of court of 3 judges in action under subsection holding title or amendment made by title or provision unconstitutional <P>
<A HREF = "SPP164.HTM#AO3757130"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Appeal to be filed not more than 20 days after entry of judgment, decree or order <P>
<A NAME = "AK3759"></A><H3><CENTER>TITLE VI--EFFECT ON OTHER LAWS</CENTER>
</H4><P><A NAME = "AK3762"></A><H3>SEC. 601. APPLICABILITY OF CONSENT DECREES AND OTHER LAW.
</H3><P><A NAME = "AE13440"></A><A HREF = "SPP165.HTM#AO376716"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Conduct or activity being subject to restriction or obligation imposed by AT&T Consent Decree to be subject to restrictions and obligations imposed by Communications Act of 1934 as amended by Act and not subject to restrictions and obligations imposed by Consent Decree <P>
<A NAME = "AE13450"></A><A HREF = "SPP165.HTM#AO376914"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Conduct or activity being subject to restriction or obligation imposed by GTE Consent Decree to be subject to restrictions and obligations imposed by Communications Act of 1934 as amended by Act and not subject to restrictions and obligations imposed by Consent Decree <P>
<A NAME = "AE13460"></A><A HREF = "SPP165.HTM#AO377114"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Conduct or activity being subject to restriction or obligation imposed by McCaw Consent Decree to be subject to restrictions and obligations imposed by Communications Act of 1934 as amended by Act and subsection of section and not subject to restrictions and obligations imposed by Consent Decree <P>
<A NAME = "AE13470"></A><A HREF = "SPP165.HTM#AO377514"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Provided in paragraphs and impair or supersede applicability of antitrust laws <P>
<A NAME = "AE13480"></A><A HREF = "SPP165.HTM#AO37775"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>REPEAL-Subsection of section 221 repealed <P>
<A NAME = "AE13490"></A><A HREF = "SPP165.HTM#AO37795"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>CLAYTON ACT-Section 7 of Clayton Act amended in last paragraph by striking Federal Communications Commission <P>

