</UL><P>
<H3>`SEC. 11.  REGULATORY REFORM.
</H3><P>
<UL><P>`(a) BIENNIAL REVIEW OF REGULATIONS- In every even-numbered year
(beginning with 1998), the Commission--
</UL><P>
<UL><UL><P>`(1) shall review<A NAME = "AO24508"></A><A NAME = "AS24509"></A> all regulations issued under this Act in effect
at the time of the review that apply to the operations or activities of any
provider of telecommunications<A NAME = "BB245062"></A><A HREF = "SPP112.HTM#BB246976"><img src="CIRCLINK.GIF"></A> service; and
</UL></UL><P>
<UL><UL><P>`(2) shall determine whether any such regulation is no longer
necessary in the public interest as the result of meaningful economic competition
between providers of such service.
</UL></UL><P>

