<HR WIDTH=64% ALIGN=center SIZE=3>
<BR>
<BR>
<H2>The London Club</H2>
<P>
<B>The London Club </B>exists to offer third party liability insurance
to shipowners,
operators and charterers on a mutual,
non-profit basis. 
<P>
The London Club is one of the leading P&amp;I Clubs in the International Group, which
together insure the vast majority of the world's
merchant shipping, and handle claims ranging from crew sickness or cargo damage to
the full cost of oil spills such as the <I>Sea Empress</I>.
<P>
The Club provides <A HREF="re_p_i.htm"<A HREF="re_p_i.htm" onMouseOver="self.status='Information on the insurance cover offered by the London Club'; return true"> P&amp;I </A> ("protection and indemnity")
insurance to the owners and operators of a fleet
totalling more than thirty million gross tons. These are drawn from shipowning
countries which include Chile, China, Greece, Hong
Kong, India, Israel, Italy, Korea, Malaysia, Monaco, Singapore, Turkey, UK and USA.
The Club has strong membership in Greece and
the Far East, and a growing presence in Latin America. Almost half of the membership
is also covered by the <A HREF="re_p_i.htm"<A HREF="re_p_i.htm" onMouseOver="self.status='See our page of information on the insurance cover offered'; return true"> FD&amp;D </A> Class ("freight, demurrage and defence") which the Club offers.
<P>
Strong financial reserves enable the Club to offer Members stable calls, which are
backed by the massive reinsurance capacity of
the International Group of P&amp;I Clubs.
<P>
<H3>On this website</H3>
<P>The Club's <A HREF="newslets.htm" onMouseOver="self.status='The London Club News and StopLoss Bulletins'; return true">newsletters</A>, the bi-monthly <I>London Club
News,</I> and quarterly <I>StopLoss Bulletin,</I> will be posted to this site. These
informative and entertaining newsletters highlight
some of the perils of the marine industries,
and the steps taken by the London Club to protect its Members.
<P>
<A HREF="press.htm" onMouseOver="self.status='Magazine articles by London Club Managers'; return true"> Magazine articles</A> by the senior management of A Bilbrough & Co will appear from time to time on the site. While these articles do not necessarily reflect the official policy of the Club, they do offer a highly-informed perspective on the changing world of marine insurance.
<P>
To contact Club's Managers or Correspondents in any of 300 ports around the world, for further information, or if you have any comments about the site, please visit the <A HREF="contact.htm" onMouseOver="self.status='Contact info for the Managers and Correspondents worldwide'; return true"> Contact</A> page
<P>
Along with administrative matters such as the site's updating schedule, a selection of <A HREF="re_site.htm#Links" onMouseOver="self.status='Selected web sites relevant to the marine industries'; return true"> links</A> to other maritime web sites is available in the <A HREF="re_site.htm" onMouseOver="self.status='About this site'; return true"> About this
site</A> section.
</font><BR>
