<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>London Club - A Bilbrough &amp; Co</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#A4C8F0" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#400080" ALINK="#004000">
<B><FONT SIZE=+2>The</FONT> <FONT SIZE=+6>L</FONT><FONT SIZE=+2>ondon Steam-Ship Owners' Mutual Insurance Association - </FONT><FONT SIZE=+1>(The London P&amp;I Club)</FONT></B>
<P><IMG SRC="images/re_lsso.gif" ALT="Tower Bridge" WIDTH=64 HEIGHT=64 VSPACE=6 ALIGN=RIGHT>
<H3>Management of the Club</H3>

<IMG SRC="images/abc_logo.gif" ALT="A Bilbrough flag" WIDTH=135 HEIGHT=125 HSPACE=6 ALIGN=left> 
The club is managed by <B>A. Bilbrough &amp; Co Ltd</B>.
<P>
The club Managers have built up a reputation for offering a first class service to the Members, and for taking a selective approach to underwriting. This policy is intended to reduce the risk to Members; additionally the Managers have an active ship inspection and loss prevention programme.
<P>
The club was originally managed by Sir George Hodgkinson, but in 1890 it was taken over by Arthur Bilbrough, a Liverpool shipowner and Lloyd's broker. Today, Bilbroughs is run by a team of directors which have expertise in law, insurance, accountancy and seamanship. They are supported by ninety staff in London and smaller offices in Piraeus and Hong Kong. (See "Contacting the Club" for details of the offices.) There is also a representative office in Korea and a network of over five hundred correspondents in ports around the world.
<P>
<BR><BR>

<H3>The Managers</H3>

<IMG SRC="images/ge.jpg" ALT="M G Edmiston" WIDTH=110 HEIGHT=110 ALIGN=right>
<H4>GRAHAM EDMISTON - Chairman</H4>
The fourth generation of his family in shipping, Graham was educated at
Marlborough College and Oxford University where he read law. Practised as a
Solicitor before joining Bilbroughs in 1972 and was appointed a Director in
1975. Supervised claims handling for many of the Club's Greek Members for
several years. Set up the Greek office in 1980 and served as manager of that
office from 1986 to 1990. Was heavily involved in the handling of FD&amp;D
claims for many years and was a Member of the Documentary Committees for
BIMCO and the UK Chamber of Shipping from 1988 to 1995. Appointed Chairman in 1995.
<P><BR>
<H4>BRYAN GAZE - Deputy Chairman</H4>
<IMG SRC="images/bg.jpg" ALT="B C Gaze" WIDTH=110 HEIGHT=110 ALIGN=left>
Educated at Eltham College and University of Wales where he read Electrical
Engineering. After qualifying as a Chartered Accountant, Bryan joined
Bilbroughs in 1972 and was appointed a Director in 1976.
Has overall responsibility for the Club's financial affairs and supervises
investment management of the Club's funds. Introduced the computerisation of
the Club's accounting procedures and claims information recording. Represents
the Club on the International Group reinsurance sub-committee, was until recently the chairman of
the International Group Regulatory Affairs and Accounting Standards
sub-committee, and is a Member of the Group panel which oversees its budget.
<P><BR>
<H4>LANCE JOHNSON - Marketing &amp; Claims Director</H4>
<IMG SRC="images/lj.jpg" ALT="L L Johnston" WIDTH=110 HEIGHT=110 ALIGN=left>
Educated at Sevenoaks School. Associate of the Chartered Insurance Institute.
Lance joined Bilbroughs in 1965. Assistant to Fred Kentfield (a former Senior
Director) for 6 years. Served in the Hong Kong office from 1976 to 1978.
Appointed a Director in 1980 and served as Resident Director in Hong Kong
from 1982 to 1988.
<P> 
Although he has considerable claims handling experience, he is now mainly
engaged in marketing the Club in the Far East for which area he has overall
responsibility, and in co-ordinating marketing activity worldwide.
<P><BR>

<IMG SRC="images/if.jpg" ALT="I A M Ferguson" WIDTH=110 HEIGHT=110 ALIGN=right>
<H4>IAN FERGUSON - Claims Director</H4>
Educated at Cranleigh School and Keele University where he read Law and Politics.
<P>
Ian joined Bilbroughs in 1976 after qualifying as a Barrister. He served in the Hong Kong office from 1979 to 1982 and again from 1984 to 1994. He was
appointed a Director in 1987. He has considerable experience in the
management and negotiation of large P&amp;I and FD&amp;D claims involving a wide
variety of jurisdiction and laws.
<P>
He represents the Association on the BIMCO and UK chamber of Shipping
Documentary Committees and certain International Group sub-committees.
<P><BR>
<IMG SRC="images/ph.jpg" ALT="P S Hinton" WIDTH=110 HEIGHT=110 ALIGN=right>
<H4>PAUL HINTON - Claims Director</H4>
Educated at St. Dunstan's College and City of London Polytechnic, where he
obtained a First Class Honours Degree in Maritime Studies. Served at sea as a
Navigating Officer for 9 years mainly with BP Tanker Co.
<P>
Paul joined Bilbroughs in 1976. Served in the Hong Kong office from 1978
to 1980. Appointed a Director in 1987. Has considerable claims handling
experience and supervises claims handling for many of the Club's Greek,
South American, US and European Members.
<P><BR>
<H4>MICHAEL HILL - Senior Underwriting Director
</H4>
<IMG SRC="images/mh.jpg" ALT="M D M Hill" WIDTH=110 HEIGHT=110 ALIGN=left>
Educated at Aldenham School and St. Luke's College, Exeter. Mike joined
Bilbroughs in 1978. After an initial period in claims handling, transferred to the
Underwriting Department where he initially dealt with the Far East and the
USA but now has overall underwriting responsibility for the Club's world-wide
Membership. Appointed a Director in 1992.
<P>
<BR><BR>
<BR><BR>
<BR><BR>
<BR>
<A NAME="Contacting"></A>
<H2>Contacting the Club's Managers</H2>
<BR>
Staff at A Bilbrough &amp; Co are constantly available to assist Members of the Club.
<P>
Click here for a <A HREF="contact.htm" onMouseOver="self.status='Directory of contacts and correspondents'; return true"> directory of contacts</A> at the offices of A Bilbrough &amp; Co and its correspondents around the world.
